item.title: Need help
item.dc:creator: @Tom Tom
item.description:
@Tom wrote:

You told us on the IRC it said ‘no response from server’. Please make your mind up. If it says error connecting to server then I suggest you review the way you’ve made your server, and ensure you’re connecting to the correct IP.

Frequent problems people usually run into are portforwarding, you might want to look at the below.

moparisthebest.com

moparisthebest.com

programming, irc, cars


moparisthebest.com

moparisthebest.com

programming, irc, cars

If it says no response from server then you should ensure that the server is not rejecting the connection, you could be ipbanned or the server is just rejecting the client you’re trying to connect with. Check for any error messages on the black box which appears when you run the server.

You need to also make sure you’re using correct clients/servers. Example: a 317 client will connect to a 317 server, a 508 client and a 317 server will not connect. Most servers/clients tell you this when you download them.
